The arrival of spring in Texas and other states in the U.S. heartland
brings with it the tornado season.  To keep loss of life and property
damage to a minimum, the National Weather Service and emergency
personnel advise the following: a.  Make safety plans before a tornado
strikes.

b. Know the difference between a tornado watch (conditions suitable
for tornado development) and a tornado warning (one has already
developed.)

c. A warning means to take cover immediately and stay inside.  If in a
car or mobile home, take cover in a ditch.  If at home, stay in the
basement or a shelter.</SUM>

