The following is a summary of the tornadoes that swept through
Huntsville, Alabama and a number of other states on 15 and 16
November, 1989:

In Huntsville, rescuers continued to search for victims of a tornado
that left 17 dead, 463 injured and 1000 homeless.  There was no
warning when it hit at rush hour.  Some residents had their own
personal accounts of the tornado's fury.  Huntsville's officials were
preparing a request for federal aid.

Tornado watches were issued for the Northeast.  Other tornadoes struck
over a period of 48 hours in the Mid-Atlantic, Mid-West and Southeast
states.</SUM>

